  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a multi-site hemolysis measurement campaign conducted across five clinical perfusion centres, which the assessment narrative characterises as providing rigorous, controlled experimental benchmarks for the relative hemolysis index. The campaign is cited extensively in the output-comparison and test-conditions factor rationales as fulfilling the controlled-experiment requirement mandated by the governing verification requirement.",
