        "type": "Activity",
        "activityType": "observational-study",
        "name": "Multi-site clinical perfusion centre hemolysis observational study",
        "description": "Hemolysis data were collected prospectively at five cardiopulmonary bypass perfusion centres using standard clinical monitoring protocols. No randomisation, blinding, or experimental manipulation of operating conditions was performed; centres recorded RHI under their routine clinical flow-speed settings. Data were pooled and provided to the modelling team as a validation dataset."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-mesh-sensitivity",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh sensitivity and discretisation error quantification",
      "description": "Three mesh refinement levels (coarse 2.1M, medium 5.8M, fine 14.2M cells) were applied to the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry. GCI-based discretisation error for shear-stress-derived haemolysis index was 3.1% on the fine mesh, within the accepted threshold for MRL 2.",
      "wasGeneratedBy": {
